Former President Shimon Peres of Israel has passed away at the age of 93. He was regarded as one of Israel's founding fathers and a beloved statesman. Peres had a political career that spanned over six decades and inspired generations with his commitment to his country. He was known for his efforts in making the desert bloom and for his role in securing Israel against its adversaries. Peres was also a peacemaker, famously participating in a historic handshake between Israel and Palestine. He had a close relationship with the United States and was considered a wise and steadying presence during difficult times. Peres was known for his optimism and his ability to find hope in any situation. His passing is a great loss for Israel and the world.